The paper focuses on security issues in Cognitive Radio (CR) networks, which are wireless networks that utilize limited spectrum resources. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). The paper also discusses detection and defense approaches, which are related to network infrastructure and communication protocols, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) and cs.IT (Information Theory). The proposed defense approach involves admission control, which is related to system control and optimization, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.SY (Systems and Control). Finally, the paper presents illustrative results that involve signal processing and data analysis, suggesting that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
